**Here’s everything you need to *survive* Bali 🐚

trust me, you don’t want your tropical getaway ending in the ER 🛵💥🚑**

So here’s your *must-have* to avoid turning your vacay into a medical drama:
 

• Motion sickness tablets 
- 💊 Painkillers 
• Antihistamines (for surprise allergies)
• 💧 Antacid and ORS (for the Bali belly)
• 🚑 Gauze, band-aids, tape and antiseptic solutions

Always make sure to keep in check with your doctor before taking any medications and ofcourse, don’t forget to have some fun ;) <3

latestPosts.caption:
Soft launching “my career change” 🤷🏻‍♀️

It’s been a year since I came back to my hometown and since then so many things have changed.

- I graduated in a degree that took me years to prepare for with so many sleepless nights and tearful eyes. 👩‍🎓 

- I took the decision of heading right into work at a hospital without any breaks because as my mom says “An idle mind is a devil’s workshop”. 🩺 

- After months of working there I found it difficult to find any sort of enjoyment in what I do. Yes, it felt good to talk to patients and watch them heal but I always thought what about me? 

-  and then the next thing I know, I have secured another job that answered that question! 🙋‍♀️ 

-  and then my hardwork paid off and I was able to travel abroad with the opportunities of taking myself out of my comfort zone ✈️ 

- I kicked out the fear of water and went into the ocean (ofcourse with precautions) to witness things that I had only seen on screens 🌊

- I pushed myself to the limits and hiked for the first time to the top of hill wearing questionable shoes and a skirt because if not now then when? ⛰️ 

- Lastly during the entire year I struggled with feeling uncomfortable in my body but now I’d say I’m on a path to get back what I lost and lose what I unwillingly gained. 💪🏻

Now coming to the question I am always asked..

Will I go back to medicine?

Well, I don’t know what the future holds, but I know who holds the future.
